\b7NAME\c9
\tpermutil - utilities for working with file permissions

\b7DESCRIPTION\c9a
\tThis library provides a simple mechanism for working with standard POSIX permissions.

\b7FUNCTIONS
\t\b2permutil.tostring\b4(\b7perms\c9:\b5number\b4)\c9: \b3string\c9
\t\tTakes a 9-bit integer and parses it into a string in the form used by \b7ls\c9(\b71\c9).

\t\b2permutil.hasPermission\b4(\b7perms\c9:\b5number\c9, \b7p\c9:\b3string\c9[, \b7s\c9:\b3string\c9]\b4)\c9
\t\tLooks for the specified permission in the provided set of permissions.  \b3p\c9 specifies the permission itself (`r', `w', or `x'), and \b3s\c9, if provided, specifies the subset of permissions to search for \b3p\c9 (`owner', `group', or `other').  For example, \b2permutil.hasPermission\b4(\b5109\c9, \b3"r"\c9, \b3"owner"\b4)\c9 returns \b5true\c9.

